========================================================================
  DIAGNOSTIC: rhythm inertness probe  (Tier 4.3 — THE HONEST RISK)
========================================================================

  500 steps per workload. Field runs AS-IS — no heartbeat.
  Question: under real load, does phase_coherence move off 0.5
  enough for the rhythm coupling to change subjective time?

  (k_agitation ships at 0.0, so the negative-valence quadrant cannot
   contribute footprint here regardless of pc — only the flow term
   can register. This is by design; the sign sweep is a separate run.)

  ── canonical  (n=495) ───────────────────────────────
     phase_coherence : mean=0.9377  std=0.0124  min=0.8684  max=0.9796
     |pc_c| > 0.3    : 100.0% of steps off neutral
     flow-eligible   : 100.0% of steps (pc_c>0 & arousal>0 & valence>0)
     footprint vs 4.2: mean=0.02043  max=0.15876  (|dilation - dilation@pc=0.5|)
     VERDICT         : ACTIVE     (coupling meaningfully bends subjective time)

  ── adversarial  (n=495) ─────────────────────────────
     phase_coherence : mean=0.9598  std=0.0126  min=0.8640  max=0.9802
     |pc_c| > 0.3    : 100.0% of steps off neutral
     flow-eligible   : 100.0% of steps (pc_c>0 & arousal>0 & valence>0)
     footprint vs 4.2: mean=0.02084  max=0.15137  (|dilation - dilation@pc=0.5|)
     VERDICT         : ACTIVE     (coupling meaningfully bends subjective time)

  ── mixed  (n=495) ───────────────────────────────────
     phase_coherence : mean=0.9614  std=0.0099  min=0.9025  max=0.9874
     |pc_c| > 0.3    : 100.0% of steps off neutral
     flow-eligible   : 100.0% of steps (pc_c>0 & arousal>0 & valence>0)
     footprint vs 4.2: mean=0.02093  max=0.16329  (|dilation - dilation@pc=0.5|)
     VERDICT         : ACTIVE     (coupling meaningfully bends subjective time)

========================================================================
  READING THE RESULT
========================================================================

  If footprint ≈ 0 and pc clusters at 0.5: the coupling is INERT under
  tested load — the field settles and produces no rhythm to couple. That
  is a genuine finding about the Chronos Core, not a bug, and it mirrors
  the Tier 4.2 result that the emotional gradient is never exercised at
  rest. It does NOT justify a synthetic heartbeat. If a later tier wants
  rhythm at rest, it must earn it without breaking the sink isolation.

  If footprint is non-trivial: the field DOES generate measurable rhythm
  under load and 4.3 is doing real work — proceed to the k_flow sweep to
  tune compression depth.

